    <!-- What it is -->
    <section class="section fade-up fade-up-5">
        <h2>What Is Parachute?</h2>
        <p>Parachute is your daily note-taking system and your AI chatbot, built on your own infrastructure, connected by an intelligent graph database that gives your whole system coherent memory.</p>
        <p>You write, you think, you capture voice notes on walks. In the background, your AI works&mdash;remembering your projects, your people, your patterns. <strong>Instead of you learning the system, the system learns you.</strong></p>
    </section>

    <!-- Two Paths -->
    <section class="section fade-up fade-up-6">
        <h2>Two Ways In</h2>

        <div class="products paths">
            <div class="product">
                <p class="path-label">Start here</p>
                <h3>Parachute Daily</h3>
                <p>Voice-first journaling that works completely offline. Capture thoughts on walks, in the car, wherever you think. Your notes stay on your device in a local graph database you own.</p>
                <p>Coming soon: daily reflections that surface what mattered, patterns you didn't notice, and connections across your thinking.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="product">
                <p class="path-label">Go deeper</p>
                <h3>Parachute Computer</h3>
                <p>Your own AI infrastructure. Chat with full context across every conversation. A knowledge graph that grows with you. Agents that work while you think. Runs on your machine, open source.</p>
                <p>If you've used Claude Code, think of this as Claude Code for your whole life&mdash;not just your codebase.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p>Everything in Daily flows into your Computer's memory. No migration, no export. The same files, the same graph. Start simple, grow when you're ready.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- How It Works -->
    <section class="section">
        <h2>How It Works</h2>
        <div class="architecture-diagram">
You -> App (Flutter) -> Parachute Computer -> AI
                              |
                        Brain (memory)
                         /         \
                      Chat        Notes</div>
        <p>One app. One server. One memory. Your data lives on your machine in a local embedded graph database&mdash;portable, exportable, entirely yours. <a href="/architecture/">Read the full docs &rarr;</a></p>
