    <!-- Principles -->
    <section class="section">
        <h2>Principles</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Local-first.</strong> Your data lives on your device in a local graph database. If we disappeared tomorrow, your data would still be there&mdash;portable, exportable, entirely yours.</li>
            <li><strong>Voice-first.</strong> Talking is often more natural than typing. We meet people where their thinking actually happens.</li>
            <li><strong>Open source as trust.</strong> The only way to deserve trust with personal thinking is transparency. You can see exactly what the software does.</li>
            <li><strong>AI as partner.</strong> The goal isn't to automate your thinking. It's to help you think more clearly, remember more completely, make connections you might have missed.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Get Started -->
    <section class="section">
        <h2>Get Started</h2>
        <p>Parachute is in active development with a small community of early users. The code is open source and on GitHub.</p>
        <div class="product">
            <h3>Explore on GitHub</h3>
            <div class="code-inline">
                <code>git clone https://github.com/OpenParachutePBC/parachute-computer.git</code>
            </div>
            <p>Requires Python 3.11+ and a Claude OAuth token (<code>claude setup-token</code>) for the server. Flutter for the app. Daily works offline with no server needed.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

